# NACOS University Chapter — Product Requirements Document

**Version:** 1.0  
**Status:** Finalized for Development  
**Stack:** Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS (Frontend) · Node.js + Express (Backend) · Supabase (DB + Storage) · Render (API Hosting) · Vercel (Frontend Hosting)

---

## 1. Product Overview

An open-source full-stack web platform for the university NACOS (National Association of Computing Students) chapter, currently serving the Computer Science department with architecture ready for multi-department expansion. The platform consists of a public-facing landing site and a gated member portal called **The Hub**.

### 1.1 Goals
- Become the most functional and well-designed NACOS chapter website in Nigeria
- Provide real, daily-use value to members through The Vault and credit economy
- Replace fragmented WhatsApp communication with structured announcements and events
- Build a living alumni network that grows in value over time
- Maintain security and data integrity at every layer

### 1.2 Non-Goals (V1)
- Mobile native app
- Department dues collection
- Third-party payment integration
- Mentorship matching system

---

## 2. Users & Roles

| Role | Access | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `guest` | Public site only | Non-members, visitors |
| `member` | Full Hub access | Active students and staff |
| `alumni` | Hub (read-mostly) | Graduated members |
| `executive` | Hub + Executive Portal | Assigned per session by super admin |
| `super_admin` | Full system access | Permanent, no expiry |

### 2.1 Role Notes
- Executives are regular members elevated per academic session by super admin
- Executive assignment displays across the system on their profile and the About page
- Alumni badges show offices held, awards, and NACOS service history (added by admin/executives at the time)
- Alumni can be reached via their included socials — no internal mentorship request system

---

## 3. Onboarding Flow

No open signups. Access is invite-only via matric-number-tied PIN.

```
1. Super admin enters verified matric number into the system
2. System generates a unique 8-character alphanumeric PIN (hashed in DB)
   - Tied to that specific matric number
   - Expires in 72 hours
   - Admin can set level_of_entry and admission_type at generation
3. Admin hands PIN to the verified owner
4. User visits /hub/register
   - Step 1: Enter matric number + PIN (validated server-side)
   - Step 2: Set email, password, display name
   - Step 3: Fill profile (photo optional at this stage)
   - Email verification link sent on completion
5. PIN marked as used — permanently invalidated
6. Account active after email verification
```

**Edge cases:**
- Expired PIN → admin regenerates, old one permanently invalidated
- Already-used PIN → rejected
- Matric mismatch → silent rejection (security)
- Transfer students → `level_of_entry` pre-set at PIN generation (200, 300)
- Repeat/suspended students → same level, different expected graduation year, `academic_status` tracks state
- Readmitted students → `admission_type: readmission`

---

## 4. Landing Site (7 Pages)

All content sections editable via admin CMS. Draft/publish workflow for blog and news.

### 4.1 Pages

**Home**
- Hero section (editable headline, subtext, CTA buttons)
- About NACOS teaser
- Upcoming events preview (pulls from events table, max 3)
- Latest blog/news preview (max 3)
- Gallery teaser (latest 6 images)
- The Hub teaser section (sells the portal to non-members)
- Cyberspace community teaser with social links
- WhatsApp community join link (prominent CTA)
- Active announcement banner (if any, from announcements table)

**About**
- Mission and vision (CMS-editable)
- Current executives (pulls from executive_assignments for current session)
- Faculty & staff (from faculty_staff table)
- Level advisors (from faculty_staff table, filtered by role)
- Department info (current department name from site_settings)

**The Pulse (Events & News)**
- Upcoming and past events with RSVP button (members only, prompts login for guests)
- News feed
- Filter by type/date

**Contact**
- Contact details (CMS-editable: email, phone, office location)
- Social links (all platforms including Cyberspace socials)
- WhatsApp community link
- Contact form (sends email via Resend)

**Blogs & Newsletters**
- Published blog posts (paginated)
- Tag filtering
- Individual post pages `/blog/:slug`
- Newsletter signup (email collection, no external service needed — stored in DB)

**Navbar / Footer / Mobile**
- Sticky navbar with active state
- Social links in footer (NACOS socials + Cyberspace socials)
- WhatsApp community join button
- Hamburger menu for mobile
- The Hub CTA (prominent, contextual)
- Privacy Policy and Terms of Use links in footer

**Gallery**
- Masonry or grid layout
- Filterable by event/tag
- Lightbox on click
- High-quality images served via Supabase CDN with optimization params

### 4.2 Cyberspace Community Integration
- Dedicated teaser section on Home page
- Cyberspace social links in navbar/footer (separate from NACOS socials)
- CMS-editable Cyberspace description and links

---

## 5. The Hub (Member Portal)

### 5.1 Auth Pages
- `/hub` — Public teaser (sells the Hub)
- `/hub/login`
- `/hub/register` — Multi-step PIN-gated flow
- `/hub/forgot-password`
- `/hub/reset-password`
- `/hub/verify-email`

### 5.2 Dashboard `/hub/dashboard`
- Personalized welcome with name
- Wallet balance card
- Quick stats: total uploads, credits earned, pending upload status
- Active announcements
- Upcoming events (next 2)
- Vault leaderboard preview (top 3)
- Recent notifications (last 5)

### 5.3 The Vault `/hub/vault`
- Filter: department, level, semester, course code/name search (full-text)
- Upload flow: course selector → file upload (PDF only, max 10MB) → title + description
- Approved uploads grid/list with download button
- Download count displayed per upload
- My Uploads tab (status: pending, approved, rejected with reason)
- Flag button on each upload (with reason)
- Credit reward shown on approval notification

### 5.4 Wallet `/hub/wallet`
- Balance display (prominent)
- Transfer form: recipient search (by matric or display name), amount, **required remark**
- Transaction history: filterable by type (credit, debit, transfer_in, transfer_out, redemption, upload_reward)
- Each transaction: type icon, amount, remark, actor, timestamp, running balance

### 5.5 Marketplace `/hub/marketplace`
- Item grid with type badge (Digital / Physical)
- Price in credits, stock count
- Redeem flow: item detail → confirm → **required remark** → deduct credits
- Digital items: delivery content shown immediately on fulfillment
- My Orders tab (pending, fulfilled, cancelled)

### 5.6 Events `/hub/events`
- Published events list with RSVP toggle
- RSVP cap shown (X spots left if limit set)
- Event detail `/hub/events/:id` (full description, location, RSVP)
- My RSVPs tab

### 5.7 Alumni Directory `/hub/alumni`
- Card grid: photo, name, graduation year, department
- Social links on card (LinkedIn, GitHub, email if visible)
- NACOS service badges: offices held, awards (added by admin)
- Filter by graduation year, level of entry
- Clicking card opens full profile

### 5.8 Messages `/hub/messages`
- Conversation list (most recent first)
- Chat window with real-time feel (polling or Supabase realtime)
- New conversation: search member by name or matric
- System creates conversation only if one doesn't already exist between two users

### 5.9 Notifications `/hub/notifications`
- Full list, unread highlighted
- Types: vault_approved, vault_rejected, credit_received, transfer, order_update, announcement, message, event_reminder
- Mark individual or all as read
- Notification bell in navbar with unread count badge

### 5.10 Profile & Settings `/hub/profile`
- View/edit: display name, bio, profile photo
- Social links: LinkedIn, GitHub, personal email visibility toggle
- Academic info display (read-only): level, year of admission, expected graduation, admission type
- Change password
- Notification preferences

### 5.11 Executive & Admin Portal `/hub/admin`
Access gated by `executive` or `super_admin` role.

**Overview**
- Member count, active users, total uploads, total credits distributed
- Pending vault queue count
- Pending orders count

**Member Management**
- Search, filter by role/level/status
- View profile, change role, suspend/reactivate
- View wallet balance and transaction history of any member

**PIN Management** *(super_admin only)*
- Generate PIN for matric number
- Set level_of_entry, admission_type at generation
- View generated pins (hashed — not reversible, but status visible)
- Invalidate unexpired pins

**Vault Moderation**
- Pending uploads queue
- Preview PDF, view metadata
- Approve (triggers credit reward + notification) or reject (with reason)
- Manage courses (add/edit/delete course codes)
- View flagged uploads

**Marketplace Management**
- Add/edit/delete items (name, description, price, stock, type, image, digital content)
- Order fulfillment queue (mark as fulfilled with note)
- View all orders

**Credit Management**
- Issue credits to individual member or bulk (CSV upload of matric numbers + amounts)
- Set upload reward rate (credits per approved upload)
- Set transfer limits and cooldown period
- Every issuance requires a remark

**Events Management**
- Create/edit/delete events
- Set RSVP limit
- View RSVP list with member details
- Export RSVP list (CSV)

**CMS Editor**
- Edit all landing page sections (hero, about, contact, Cyberspace teaser)
- Manage blog posts (draft/publish)
- Manage news items
- Manage gallery (upload/delete images, tag by event)
- Manage faculty/staff/level advisors
- Manage announcements (set target: public/members/all, set expiry)

**Executive Assignment** *(super_admin only)*
- Assign member to executive role for a session with title
- View current and past executive assignments
- Revoke assignment (returns member to member role)

**Site Settings** *(super_admin only)*
- Current department name and code
- Current academic session
- WhatsApp community link
- Social links (NACOS + Cyberspace)
- Upload reward rate
- Transfer max limit and cooldown
- Privacy policy and terms content (editable)

