## 6. Security Requirements

### 6.1 Authentication
- Passwords: bcrypt with cost factor ≥ 12
- JWT access tokens: 15-minute expiry, signed with RS256 (asymmetric)
- Refresh tokens: 7-day expiry, stored as httpOnly Secure SameSite=Strict cookie, hashed in DB
- One refresh token family per user (rotation + reuse detection — old token used = full family revoked)
- Email verification required before any Hub access
- PIN: bcrypt-hashed in DB, single-use, 72-hour expiry, constant-time comparison

### 6.2 Authorization
- Every protected route checks JWT validity and role
- Row-Level Security (RLS) enabled on all Supabase tables as a second layer
- Executives cannot perform super_admin-only actions (PIN generation, role assignment, site settings)
- Users can only access their own wallet, transactions, messages

### 6.3 Input & API Security
- All inputs validated and sanitized server-side (Zod schemas)
- File uploads: MIME type check + magic byte validation (PDFs only in Vault)
- File size limits enforced server-side (not just client)
- Rate limiting on all auth endpoints (express-rate-limit): login (5/15min), register (3/hour), forgot-password (3/hour)
- Rate limiting on file upload endpoints
- CORS: whitelist only the Vercel frontend domain
- Helmet.js for HTTP security headers
- SQL injection not possible via Supabase parameterized queries — never string-concatenate queries
- All error responses use generic messages (never expose internals)

### 6.4 Data Protection
- No sensitive data in JWT payload (only user_id and role)
- Wallet balance updated only via DB transactions (never direct update — always via ledger insert + balance update in a single transaction)
- Transfer: sender balance check, debit sender, credit receiver — atomic DB transaction
- Supabase storage: private buckets for vault PDFs (signed URLs with expiry), public bucket for images
- Signed download URLs for vault files (expire after 1 hour, generated per request)
- No raw file paths exposed in API responses

### 6.5 Monitoring & Incident Response
- Structured logging (Winston or Pino) — log all auth events, admin actions, errors
- Never log passwords, tokens, or PII
- Failed login attempts logged with IP (for future rate limit or lockout logic)
- Supabase daily backups (included in free tier)

---

## 7. Legal & Compliance

### 7.1 Privacy Policy
- What data is collected (name, matric, email, academic info, usage data)
- How it is used (authentication, platform features, communications)
- Who can see it (admins, executives for moderation, alumni directory visibility is user-controlled)
- Data retention (accounts inactive for 2+ years after graduation may be archived)
- User rights (request deletion via contact email)
- No data sold to third parties, ever
- Hosted at `/privacy-policy` (linked in footer)

### 7.2 Terms of Use
- Acceptable use policy (no harassment via messages, no fake past questions)
- Wallet and credits are non-monetary (no cash value, non-transferable outside the system)
- NACOS reserves the right to suspend accounts violating community standards
- Hosted at `/terms` (linked in footer)

### 7.3 Cookie Policy
- Only essential cookies used (refresh token httpOnly cookie)
- No tracking cookies, no analytics that requires consent
- Simple cookie notice on first visit

---

## 8. Performance Requirements

- API response time: < 300ms for standard endpoints, < 1s for file operations
- Image delivery: Supabase CDN with transformation params (`?width=800&quality=80`) — no full-size images served to frontend
- PDF delivery: signed URLs direct from Supabase CDN — no API proxy
- Render cold start mitigation: cron-job.org pings `/health` endpoint every 10 minutes
- Supabase pause mitigation: same cron ping hits a lightweight Supabase query every 10 minutes
- Frontend: Next.js Image component for all images, lazy loading, ISR for public content pages

---

## 9. Data & Deletion Policy

- **CMS content:** Any section can be updated. Old values are overwritten (no versioning in V1)
- **Gallery:** Images can be deleted by admin — file deleted from Supabase Storage bucket (no orphaned files)
- **Vault uploads:** Rejected or removed uploads delete the file from storage
- **User accounts:** Soft delete (is_active: false). Files and transactions remain for integrity. Hard delete available to super_admin only
- **Wallet transactions:** Append-only. Never deleted. Immutable ledger
- **Notifications:** Soft-clearable by user. Hard-deleted after 90 days
- **Messages:** Deletable by sender (soft delete — shows "message deleted")
- **Marketplace items:** Soft delete (is_available: false) to preserve order history

---

## 10. Newsletter Subscribers

- Email collected on landing page newsletter form
- Stored in `newsletter_subscribers` table (email, subscribed_at, is_active)
- Admin can export list (CSV) from admin portal
- Unsubscribe link in any email sent to subscribers
- No third-party email marketing service in V1

---

## 11. Out of Scope (V1)

- Push notifications (web push)
- Real-time chat (polling acceptable in V1, Supabase realtime can be added in V2)
- Department dues / payment processing
- Mentorship request system
- Mobile app
- Multi-department UI (architecture is ready, UI toggle is V2)
